article.description:
Boo Davis scored 26 points and Joah Tucker 24 as the 11th-seeded Panthers
upset No. 6 Oklahoma, 82-74, in a first-round game in the
Minneapolis Region.
article.headline: Davis, Tucker lead No. 11 UW-Mil. past No. 6 Sooners
article.linkText: Boo-yaa: Davis leads UW-Mil. in upset over Oklahoma
article.story: NORMAN, Okla. (AP) -- Nate Carter had 18 points and 10 rebounds to help Oklahoma beat Central Missouri 74-69 on Sunday in the exhibition game on Sunday. Longar Longar added 10 points and 12 rebounds for Oklahoma, which used an 11-4 run to take a seven-point lead with 11:53 remaining. Theo Jones led the Mules with 18 points, and Zach Wright had 16. Thunderstorms briefly knocked the power out at the Lloyd Noble Center with 3.5 seconds left in the game.
